On September 30, temporary workers demanded their wages at the Dream Space theme exhibition at the Meijiang Convention and Exhibition Center in Tianjin.
It is reported that the exhibition started on September 8 and hundreds of temporary workers were hired through an agency. According to the agency, the organizer has been withholding wages. On September 29, some people began to protest. On the afternoon of September 30, some people held banners to protest and drove away tourists. Then the police went to coordinate and let the agency and temporary workers decide to go through labor arbitration. They are currently preparing for labor arbitration.

On the evening of September 30, the live broadcast of the semi-finals of the Asian Games DOTA2 event was suddenly cancelled, which aroused strong dissatisfaction among players and anchors

On October 1, some netizens discovered that some fake Taiwanese accounts appeared in the comment section of the National Day flag-raising ceremony on Bilibili. They used traditional Chinese characters and IPs from Taiwan to express their birthday wishes to the motherland, which won praise from netizens. 
But after a few hours, when you click on the account page, you will find that these accounts have changed to mainland IPs.
